{
  "number": 1551,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/1551",
  "title": "fix(toggle): support negative numeric values for on/off",
  "body": "fixes #1537\r\n\r\nSummary:\r\n\r\nWhen the user passed values={on: -2, off: 5}, we would send to Algolia as for facet refinements: stock:-2 which would not be what we wanted to express.\r\n\r\nUsing stock:-2 as a facetRefinement is supported only if you escape\r\nthe minus sign, otherwise it's considered as negative facet refinement\r\n(remove \"-2\" from facets).\r\n\r\nNow we escape this sign when it makes sense.",
